.row
    .panel-title#page-multi
        %h2.red-strong
            Tutoring
    .bordered-panel
        %p
            While colleges evaluate applicants' extracurricular activities, students' Grade Point Average (GPA) and standardized test scores play an even more important role in the admission process. This means academic performance should be students' top priority throughout middle and high school. Sometimes this is easier said than done.
        %p
            Expert instruction and a favorable learning environment can help students improve their performance. Through consistent hourly lessons, we focus on academic improvement and confidence building. The goal: to provide students with the information and guidance they need to excel academically while reducing their stress level. 

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                Tutoring: Format & Pricing
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Group: 40 per student/hour
                            %li
                                Packet-Only: 40 per take-home study packet (no in-person instruction)
                            %li
                                Semi-private: 50 per student/hour. If only one person attends a semi-private session, the attending student pays private rate.
                            %li
                                Private (one-to-one): 75 per hour

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                Tutoring: Cancellation Policy
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                First no-show/no-notice (includes cancels within 24 hours of the scheduled session, day-of cancels, and no-shows): no charge
                            %li
                                Second no-show/no-notice (includes cancels within 24 hours of the scheduled session, day-of cancels, and no-shows): half-charge
                            %li
                                After that: full-charge
                            %li
                                During High Season, half-charge rule applies to first offense; full-charge after that.


        .service-item
            %h3.title
                Additional Information
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Groups are based on subject and availability. Space is limited.
                            %li
                                Groups fill up on a first-come, first-served basis.
                            %li
                                Weekly groups are designed to provide ongoing support throughout the school year; groups are not designed for drop-ins.
                            %li
                                Private tutoring, skill-building workshops, and AP Exam review programs are open to students from all schools and school districts. Weekly groups align with NMUSD (Newport-Mesa Unified School District) textbooks and curriculum. 
                            %li
                                As AP (Advanced Placement) courses, AP World History and AP United States History are considered college-level courses. While the ‘Advanced’ designation signals rigor, a GPA boost, and the possibility of earning college credit, it also means more work, greater responsibility, and higher expectations. Many students look back on their AP History courses as the most difficult courses they took in high school, which makes putting in the time and effort all the more important.

